// basic description:
// Obstacle Driving game:
// Game where a user controls lateral movement of a sprite using gyroscope controls to dodge incoming obstacles
//  features:
//      - players can increase or decrease speed of "driving" (really increasing speed of obstacles) to gain more points

// implementation:
// player shown his/her own screen with a point counter a top to display all players scores
// create world, player sprite, and obstacles
// add physics/functionality to world, player, and obstacles
// if collision, end scoring for player
// ^if player collision, update aliveStatus to false in db to end scoring for player
// set timeout for game length to end (~1min?) or when all players died

// Obstacle Driving game component
//   gameObject = object from firebase at path /Rooms/$roomCode/Game/
//   Scores = object from firebase at path /Rooms/$roomCode/Game/gamerules/Scores
//   playerAliveStatus = object from firebase at path /Rooms/$roomCode/Game/playerList/uid/alive
//   ^used to keep track of if player has collided with

//   winState = players(s) ighest number of objects dodged
